==English==
===Verb===
'''to flip'''
#''(transitive)'' To [[throw]] as to turn over
#:''You need to '''flip''' the pancake onto the other side''
#''(transitive)'' To put into a quick [[revolve|revolving]] motion by a [[snap]] of [[thumb]] and [[index finger]]
#:''If you can't decide which one of two options to choose, '''flip''' a coin.''
#''(intransitive)'' (''slang'') To go [[crazy]]
#:''I'd '''flip''' if anyone broke my phone''
====Synonyms====
*(1): [[turn]], [[turn over]]
*(2): [[toss]]
====Translations====
*German: [[umdrehen]] (1), [[wenden]] (1), [[werfen]] (2), [[ausflippen]] (3)

